    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pasta</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>pasta</strong> for 7-9 min (10\u201312 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-spaghetti-alfredo/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Slice your<strong> mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-spaghetti-alfredo/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a little drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced onion</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-spaghetti-alfredo/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>sliced mushroom </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 6-8 min or until golden</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-spaghetti-alfredo/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>umami seasoning</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [170ml] </span><strong>reserved starchy pasta water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>umami stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-spaghetti-alfredo/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-spaghetti-alfredo/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms are golden, add the <strong>umami stock</strong>, <strong>drained pasta </strong>and <strong>soft cheese </strong>to the pan with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>mushroom spaghetti alfredo</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-spaghetti-alfredo/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drizzle the <strong>mushroom spaghetti alfredo </strong>with your <strong>truffle oil </strong>and top with the<strong> salad </strong>and <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Finish with a grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
